					48&nbsp;&nbsp;
					<strong><a href="http://www.cameronmoll.com/mt/mt-comments.cgi?__mode=red&amp;id=7726">Thomas Baekdal</a></strong> ~ 16 September 2006 at 02:28 AM</p>
					<p>According to my analysis, practically none browse maximized at 1024x768 (you need to go above 1400√ó1050 before you see a change in browsing behavior).</p>

<p>And, in order to support about, say, 95% of the people you need to design at a maximum width of 792px. At 90% it is 840px and you only support about 80% at 960px (all based on 1024x768 resolution).</p>

<p><a href="http://www.baekdal.com/articles/Usability/actual-browser-size-preliminary/">preliminary analysis</a></p>
