					<p class="author">
					56&nbsp;&nbsp;
					<strong>James</strong> ~ 17 September 2006 at 03:41 PM</p>
					<p>Has anyone else noticed that both 750px @ 800px and 960px @ 1024px are 93.75% of the maximum screen width?</p>

<p>I prefer liquid/elastic layouts so a width of 94% might be worth trying.</p>
				</div>
				<hr/>
								<div class="comment" id="007746">
					<p class="author">
					57&nbsp;&nbsp;
					<strong><a href="http://www.cameronmoll.com/mt/mt-comments.cgi?__mode=red&amp;id=7746">Adam Osborne</a></strong> ~ 18 September 2006 at 04:33 AM</p>
					<p>We use a combination of fixed and fluid sites for our clients, but i can concur that recently(last 3 months) for the fixed width layouts we have been used 964px, 984px, 985px and 986px. I hadn&#8217;t noticed the variation before your post mentioning the optimal width, which is strange as on the 800 layouts that we have done over the last few years we have used 760px as the basis for probably all fixed width layouts.</p>

<p>Thanks for kicking my brain into gear, i&#8217;ll probably set a regular fixed with for designs now.</p>
				</div>
				<hr/>
								<div class="comment" id="007748">
