					<p>You just HAD to bring up 1024?! haha&#8230; and I just finished getting sign off from my office on a corporate redesign. All the comps are 750px wide. lol</p>

<p>Anyway great topic. I&#8217;ve been debating the transition for a while. With all the great feedback above I think i&#8217;ll have to give the 960px a try.</p>
				</div>
				<hr/>
								<div class="comment" id="007749">
					<p class="author">
					59&nbsp;&nbsp;
					<strong><a href="http://www.cameronmoll.com/mt/mt-comments.cgi?__mode=red&amp;id=7749">Dustin Wilson</a></strong> ~ 18 September 2006 at 06:43 PM</p>
					<p>You do have a good point here, actually. I made my site a long while back 1024x768, but did it at 1000 pixels wide as I looked at other sites at the time that made their websites for that resolution. I can&#8217;t really hop into it and make my site 960 pixels wide anymore, but I&#8217;ll keep that in mind when I make my next one or if I feel insane and decide to reduce the website&#8217;s width by 40.</p>
				</div>
				<hr/>
								<div class="comment" id="007750">
					<p class="author">
					60&nbsp;&nbsp;
